contextual_factors: b. Population: The claims target different human subpopulations, such as differences in age, sex, genetic background, comorbidities, ethnicity, or risk profiles.; d. Dosage or exposure duration: The same intervention is administered at different doses, frequencies, or durations.; f. Combined drug effects: The reported effect of a drug depends on its use in combination with other drugs or therapies.; i. Ambiguous expression: One or both claims contain grammatical errors or unclear referents.
